.SH NAME
ifc-to-db-info - Quick inspection of an IFC file without full import


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBifc-to-db info  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Quickly inspect an IFC file's header metadata without performing a full import.

.PP
Displays the IFC schema version, originating system, preprocessor, file
description, and entity count summary. Use this to verify a file before
importing or to check which IFC version a model uses.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for info

.PP
\fB--output-format\fP="text"
	Output format: text or json


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--help-json\fP[=false]
	Print help for all commands as machine-readable JSON


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Inspect file metadata
  ifc-to-db info model.ifc

  # Machine-readable output
  ifc-to-db info model.ifc --output-format json
.EE


